	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">Timmy112384 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">career stats</div><br />There's a reason that no NES quiz show simulator had career stats. Saving increases the cost of making cartridges by several dollars, as you need to build battery-backed RAM into the cartridge (unless you're tearing up a copy of Ultima Exodus).<br /></div>
<br />
<br />Except that now it costs nothing extra to use FlashROM, which can be saved to.  This would be especially helpful here, because you could save the LFSR(s) states, used for generating the questions.  So if you wanted, in one 'career' you could prevent any repeats until you've seen them all.

		

		</td>
