		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />With Flash memory it's also possible to modify data without having to erase the Flash each time. This is achieved by representing the data in a way that changes only involve clearing bits. A simple approach is to store the byte or word value at the beginning of a 256-byte page. If it needs to be changed, store a zero over it and put the new value just after it. This assumes the value 0 can be used as a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sentinel_value" class="postlink">sentinel value</a>.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


